ere is a series of common principles that can be extracted from the Jewish intellectual tradition that have broad, even life-changing, implications for individual and societal achievement. These principles include respect for tradition while encouraging independent, often disruptive thinking; a precise system of logical reasoning in pursuit of the truth; universal education continuing through adulthood; and living a purposeful life. The main objective of this book is to understand the historical development of these principles and to demonstrate how applying them judiciously can lead to greater intellectual productivity, a more fulfilling existence, and a more advanced society. The application of these principles to daily life can make a real and profound difference in education, productivity, and personal happiness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aJewish learning and scholarship. 0aJewsxIntellectual life. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aBible.  aEducation.  aHeritage.  aIntellectual History.  aJewish.  aJudaism.  aLiteracy.  aScholars.  aTradition.  aacademia.  aculture.  aexegesis.  alaw.  alifestyle.  aliterature.  amysticism.  aphilosophy.  arabbinics.  areligion.  ascience.  astudy.  atheology.  atorah.1 aFishbane, Simcha, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aShmidman, Michael A., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068820708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z97831106963010 cprintz978164469534040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644695357?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www